We stayed in a standard room with a king bed.	We had reservations for a double standard room.	We wanted to upgrade to a larger room, but only standard rooms are pet friendly.	We had a standard room but they do offer theme suites.	There was all the standards for a nice hotel room, there was even a coffee maker.	The hotel in all is very clean and the standard rooms are very spacious.	The standard rooms are cramped with very poor lighting.	We had a 3rd floor room, which was nice.	We just wanted more room and a bed with a pillow top mattress.	The rooms had adequate space and decorated with a medieval theme.